@section Database Changes
@cindex Database Changes

This section describes the changes to the database since Trip Server v1.
All the following changes can be implemented by running
@code{trip-server} with the @code{--upgrade} option.

@subsection pgcrypto extension
@cindex pgcrypto extension

The @code{pgcrypto} extension is needed for user password validation.
Run the following command in the Trip database:

@example
$ psql trip
CREATE EXTENSION pgcrypto;
@end example

@subsection Session Table
@cindex Session Table

There are new @code{session} and @code{session_data} tables to handle
user sessions.

@subsection Passwords
@cindex Passwords

The Blowfish algorithm appears to have been changed in PostgreSQL 13.
The following SQL will update old style encrypted passwords to work in
PostgreSQL 13.

@example
UPDATE usertable SET password = '$2a' || SUBSTRING(password, 4, 57)
WHERE password NOT LIKE '$2a%';
@end example

@subsection Handling OSM Extended Waypoint Attributes
@cindex Handling OSM Extended Waypoint Attributes

The @code{itinerary_waypoint} table's @code{color} column has been
replaced with an @code{extended_attributes} column which now stores the
extended attributes of an import from @url{https://osmand.net,OSMAnd},
including the @code{color} attribute.

